  [38;2;120;169;255m▌[0m [1mNotes[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144mAgent `style` controls reasoning: `default` is standard conversational, `react` enables ReAct (Reasoning + Acting) for step-by-step problem solving, `planner` enables advanced multi-step task decomposition.[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144mTools are referenced using `${tool.<ref_name>}` syntax, collaborators using `${agent.<ref_name>}`, and knowledge bases using `${knowledge_base.<ref_name>}`.[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144mThe `llm` field accepts either a `${model.<ref_name>}` reference or a plain string value (e.g., `groq/openai/gpt-oss-120b`). Plain values create no dependency.[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144mThe `description` field serves as the agent's system prompt and defines its core purpose, behavior, and capabilities.[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144mGuidelines provide behavioral rules with `condition` (when the guideline applies) and `action` (what the agent should do).[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144m•[0m [38;2;125;133;144m`additional_properties` supports `icon` (SVG string), `starter_prompts` (suggested conversation starters), and `welcome_content` (initial greeting).[0m

  [38;2;120;169;255m▌[0m [1mAuthoring[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144menvelope  [0m [38;2;125;133;144mA config is one or more YAML documents separated by `---`. Each has top-level `kind` and `ref_name`, then the fields below at the top level (not nested under `spec`).[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144mref_name  [0m [38;2;125;133;144mUnique handle for this resource within the config. Used to reference it from other resources, then stripped before the API call (not a schema field).[0m
    [38;2;125;133;144mreference [0m [38;2;125;133;144mReference another resource by its ref_name: `${<kind>.<ref_name>}` resolves to its id, `${<kind>.<ref_name>.<field>}` to a specific field. Values resolve late, at plan/apply time.[0m
